		<small><a href="http://entropy-bucket.blogspot.com/" title="http://entropy-bucket.blogspot.com/" class="user_homepage_display">Homepage</a> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64404058"><p>There are some good arguments about why 8 GB might not be enough for some people, but 'when I choose to download an additional browser that is known to be inefficient, and when I then use it in a way that consumes as much memory as possible, I run out of memory' really isn't one of them.</p><p>There really are people out there who are perfectly happy browsing away in Safari on their 8 GB Airs.</p><p>$200 for 8 GB of RAM is a lot. Lowering the price of your base machine by more than what you've saved by removing memory so that you have a base price that is as low as possible is another way to look at it.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64404058">
<span class="ind"></span><a id="reply_link_64404058" class="btn link" href="//hardware.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23294478&amp;op=Reply&amp;threshold=1&amp;commentsort=0&amp;mode=thread&amp;pid=64404058" onclick="D2.replyTo(64404058); return false;">Reply to This</a> 	<a href="#" class="comment_share_toggle btn link">Share</a>
