</li><li id="tree_64404074" class="comment oneline"><span class="ind"></span>
<div id="comment_status_64404074" class="commentstatus"></div>
<div id="comment_64404074" class="cw">
	<div id="comment_top_64404074" class="commentTop newcomment">
		<div class="title">
			<h4><a id="comment_link_64404074" name="comment_link_64404074" href="//hardware.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23294478&amp;cid=64404074" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(64404074)" >Swap?</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_64404074" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 64404074); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>2</a>)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~pr0nbot">pr0nbot</a>  <span class="uid"><a href="//slashdot.org/~pr0nbot">( 313417 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64404074"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64404074"><p>The OS will swap data it doesn't have space for in physical RAM to disk.<br>These days, "disk" is an SSD with a r/w speed of ~6GB/s.<br>So a 500MB inactive tab that isn't in physical RAM could theoretically swap back in in around 166ms (500MB has to be swapped out to make space, then 500MB is swapped in).<br>That's not a lot but it will be noticeable.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64404074">

</div>
</div>

